<div class="table table-100">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-5">
            <h3>Setup</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>[N+3] Round boosters, remaining go to box</li>
                <li>Set aside all 3 Gaiaformers</li>
                <li>Take QIC if printed on board</li>
                <li>Gain bonuses for research upgrades during setup</li>
                <li>1p or 2p: add a neutral satellite to final scoring tiles</li>
                <li>Snake draft with 2 mines
                    <ul>
                        <li>Home planets only</li>
                        <li>No power charges at setup</li>
                        <li>Xenos place 3rd mine after all others</li>
                        <li>Ivits place planetary institute after Xenos 3rd mine</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Choose boosters in reverse order</li>
                <li>Race specific
                    <ul>
                        <li>Taklons: brainstone</li>
                        <li>Gleens: special federation token</li>
                        <li>Ivits: six space stations</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-7">
            <h3>Notes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Gained power goes to area I; may only spend power from area III</li>
                <li>Income phase is <u>before</u> the Gaia phase</li>
                <li>Building on a Gaia planet costs 1 QIC to Terraform</li>
                <li>Building over a Gaiaformer does <u>not</u> cost 1 QIC</li>
                <li>Planets with Gaiaformers cannot be used for access to other planets (<span style="font-size: 9pt">p.12 <u>Accessibility</u></span>)</li>
                <li>Cannot take duplicate tech tiles, even if one is covered</li>
                <li>Advance in research track after taking a tech tile
                    <ul>
                        <li>top 6 basic: matching track</li>
                        <li>advanced or other basic: any</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Advanced tech
                    <ul>
                        <li>must be at level 4 or 5 of that track</li>
                        <li>must flip a federation token from green to gray</li>
                        <li>must have an uncovered standard tech tile</li>
                        <li>cannot cover advanced tech with advanced tech</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Taklons must charge power for the power gain</li>
                <li>Nevlas can "combine" power spending points for the free actions</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

